Module Hierarchy

  • oauth2client: Client library for using OAuth2, especially with Google APIs.
    • oauth2client.appengine: Utilities for Google App Engine
    • oauth2client.client: An OAuth 2.0 client.
    • oauth2client.clientsecrets: Utilities for reading OAuth 2.0 client secret files.
    • oauth2client.crypt: Crypto-related routines for oauth2client.
    • oauth2client.django_orm: OAuth 2.0 utilities for Django.
    • oauth2client.file: Utilities for OAuth.
    • oauth2client.gce: Utilities for Google Compute Engine
    • oauth2client.keyring_storage: A keyring based Storage.
    • oauth2client.locked_file: Locked file interface that should work on Unix and Windows pythons.
    • oauth2client.multistore_file: Multi-credential file store with lock support.
    • oauth2client.old_run: This module holds the old run() function which is deprecated, the tools.run_flow() function should be used in its place.
    • oauth2client.service_account: A service account credentials class.
    • oauth2client.tools: Command-line tools for authenticating via OAuth 2.0
    • oauth2client.util: Common utility library.
    • oauth2client.xsrfutil: Helper methods for creating & verifying XSRF tokens.
